{{Infobox person |name = Jean Claude Gandur |image = |caption = | birth_name = |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1949|2|18|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Grasse]], France |death_date = |death_place = |other_names = |known_for = Former Chairman and CEO of [[Addax Petroleum]] |occupation = Businessman |education = |alma_mater = [[University of Lausanne]] and [[Pantheon-Sorbonne University]] |nationality = Swiss | residence = Switzerland | salary = | net_worth = $2.3 billion | spouse = | children = }}
'''Jean Claude Gandur''' (born 18 February 1949)<ref name=LPT>{{cite web|title=Profile: Addax and Oryx Group |url=http://laspalmastrader.com/wp/profile-addax-and-oryx-group-and-joyeux-anniversaire-monsieur-gandur/ |website=LPT |accessdate=6 November 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141112180247/http://laspalmastrader.com/wp/profile-addax-and-oryx-group-and-joyeux-anniversaire-monsieur-gandur/ |archivedate=12 November 2014 |df= }}</ref> is a French-born Swiss businessman.
==Early life== Jean Claude Gandur was born in [[Grasse]], France in 1949.<ref name=Fg>{{cite web|title=Jean Claude Gandur|url=http://fg-art.org/en/jeanclaudegandur.html|website=Fg-art.org|accessdate=6 November 2014}}</ref> Gandur studied law and political science at the [[University of Lausanne]] and history at [[Pantheon-Sorbonne University]].<ref name=Fg/>
==Career== Gandur started as an oil trader. He was Chairman and CEO of [[Addax Petroleum]] until its takeover by [[Sinopec Group]] in August 2009 for $7.3 billion.<ref name=Forbes>{{cite web|title=Forbes|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/jean-claude-gandur/|accessdate=6 November 2014}}</ref>
His new Toronto-listed oil company Oryx Petroleum held its IPO in 2013, and it is developing large oilfields in Iraqi Kurdistan. As of November 2014, his net worth is $2.3 billion.<ref name=Forbes/>
