'''Kim Gap-sun'''({{ko-hhrm|김갑순|金甲淳}} May 22, 1872 – 1961) was a [[Joseon Dynasty]] bureaucrat and modern [[Korea]]n businessman, politician, and realtor.<ref>[http://koreandb.nate.com/history/people/detail?sn=8994 Kim Gap-sun] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20130627194954/http://koreandb.nate.com/history/people/detail?sn=8994 |date=2013-06-27 }} {{ko}}</ref> he was officials from slavery and large landowner of [[Chungcheongnam-do]], Japanese colonial time of Korea.

In his early life he was successively Governor of [[Buyeo County]] (1902), [[Nosung]] County (1903–1905, 1907–1910), [[Gongju]] County (1906–1907, 1910), [[Kimhwa]] County (1908–1910), and [[Asan]] county (1910–1911). His [[art name]] was Sungap, and his [[courtesy name]] was Dongwu.

