'''Telecom data intelligence (TDI)''', is the ability of a [[Telecommunications company|telco]] ([[mobile operator]] and/or [[fixed line]] carrier), to extract detailed [[Customer profiles|customer-profiling data]] from the data that is generated in the network combined with the data that is collected directly from the customers, by engaging customers online through an enhanced [[Value-added service|VAS]] customer experience.

TDI provides [[business intelligence]] to the Telco to allow them to monetise this data; and visibility to the enterprise on costs and usage while also providing a self-serve portal.

